article_title: Prairie dog removal in city contributes to owl’s decline

og.description: Retired National Park Service wilderness manager Jim Walters is deeply worried about the city's burrowing owl population. In 2008, he counted 68 breeding pairs. “Today, we only have four successful nests,” Walters says.
